    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-12-06T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-12-06T11:30:00-05:00" n="8"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d8">
                <head>8. Information Memorandum From the President’s Special Assistant (<persName
                        type="from">Rostow</persName>) to President <persName type="to"
                        >Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d8fn1">Source: Johnson Library, National
                        Security File, Country File, Middle East, Vol. I, 6/65–3/68. Secret. A
                        handwritten notation on the memorandum indicates that it was received at
                        11:55 a.m.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-12-06T11:30:00-05:00">December 6, 1967, 11:30 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Mr. President:</p>
                <p>At my request, our <persName>Hal Saunders</persName> did these two thoughtful
                    memos on: <pb facs="0046" n="18" xml:id="pg_18"/>
                    <list>
                        <item>—the choice of ahead in the Middle East;<note n="2" xml:id="d8fn2">
                                <persName corresp="#p_SHH1">Saunders</persName> sent a memorandum on
                                this subject to <persName>Rostow</persName> on December 5. It was a
                                covering memorandum for his assessment of the meaning of <persName
                                    corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName>’s November 23 speech, and
                                essentially summarized that memorandum. (Ibid.)</note>
                        </item>
                        <item>—the meaning of <persName corresp="#p_NGA1">Nasser</persName>’s Nov.
                            23 speech.<note n="3" xml:id="d8fn3">
                                <ref target="#d7">Document 7</ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>My view is: the Arabs are still confused, humiliated, looking for revenge in part
                    of their minds. But they have no long-term plan. Therefore, we must: <list>
                        <item>—struggle for an Arab-Israeli settlement:</item>
                        <item>—then follow through with policies to strengthen moderate Arabs so
                            that, with the passage of time, the attractiveness of economic and
                            social development gradually, slowly overtakes the passion for
                            revenge.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Walt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
